== Direct product in universal algebra ==
If formula_100 is a fixed signature, formula_101 is an arbitrary (possibly infinite) index set, and formula_102 is an indexed family of formula_100 algebras, the direct product formula_104 is a formula_100 algebra defined as follows:
* The universe set formula_23 of formula_107 is the Cartesian product of the universe sets formula_108 of formula_109 formally: formula_110
* For each formula_57 and each formula_57-ary operation symbol formula_113 its interpretation formula_114 in formula_107 is defined componentwise, formally. For all formula_116 and each formula_117 the formula_81th component of formula_119 is defined as formula_120 
For each formula_117 the formula_81th projection formula_123 is defined by formula_124 It is a surjective homomorphism between the formula_100 algebras formula_126

As a special case, if the index set formula_127 the direct product of two formula_100 algebras formula_129 is obtained, written as formula_130 If formula_100 contains only one binary operation formula_132 the above definition of the direct product of groups is obtained by using the notation formula_133 formula_134 Similarly, the definition of the direct product of modules is subsumed here.

== Categorical product ==

The direct product can be abstracted to an arbitrary category. In a category, given a collection of objects formula_135 indexed by a set formula_101, a product of those objects is an object formula_23 together with morphisms formula_138 for all formula_139, such that if formula_24 is any other object with morphisms formula_141 for all formula_139, there is a unique morphism formula_143 whose composition with formula_144 equals formula_145 for every formula_81. 

Such formula_23 and formula_148 do not always exist. If they exist, then formula_149 is unique up to isomorphism, and formula_23 is denoted formula_151.

In the special case of the category of groups, a product always exists. The underlying set of formula_151 is the Cartesian product of the underlying sets of the formula_108, the group operation is componentwise multiplication, and the (homo)morphism formula_138 is the projection sending each tuple to its formula_81th coordinate.

== Internal and external direct product ==
Some authors draw a distinction between an internal direct product and an external direct product. For example, if formula_23 and formula_24 are subgroups of an additive abelian group formula_36 such that formula_159 and formula_160, formula_161 and it is said that formula_36 is the &quot;internal&quot; direct product of formula_23 and formula_24. To avoid ambiguity, the set formula_165 can be referred to as the &quot;external&quot; direct product of formula_23 and formula_24.

